  "text": "The concept of distance is central in the international business literature (e.g., [CITATION_1] . The costs of overcoming distance include those of moving goods to foreign markets (geographical distance) and learning about as well as operating in new markets (cultural/psychic distance) [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Both cultural and geographical distance indicates that the firm has less control due to unfamiliarity with language, customs, and behavior. In addition, time zones and physical distance make it difficult for headquarters to exert direct control.",
